<i>- We just keep manicuring it</i>
<i>until it's perfect.</i>

00:45.462 --> 00:46.671
<i>This is fun to do.</i>

00:46.713 --> 00:48.840
You know you're at
the highest level

00:48.882 --> 00:50.592
with the highest competitors.

00:50.633 --> 00:53.094
<i>We hold ourselves</i>
<i>to a super high standard,</i>

00:53.136 --> 00:55.889
<i>but I'm never satisfied.</i>

00:55.930 --> 00:58.475
<i>- He's been pursuing</i>
<i>the perfect sheet of ice</i>

00:58.516 --> 01:00.727
<i>for almost 20 years,</i>

01:00.769 --> 01:04.105
<i>meaning events like this</i>
<i>are what he lives for.</i>

01:04.147 --> 01:06.733
<i>The best curlers</i>
<i>in the country,</i>

01:06.775 --> 01:09.819
<i>the United States</i>
<i>Olympic Trials.</i>

01:11.571 --> 01:14.282
<i>Six teams are here in Omaha.</i>

01:14.324 --> 01:16.576
<i>Only one can represent the US</i>

01:16.618 --> 01:20.080
<i>at the 2022 Olympic</i>
<i>Winter Games.</i>

01:20.121 --> 01:21.790
- Hard!
- Hard, right to it.

01:21.831 --> 01:23.958
<i>- As the defending</i>
<i>gold medalists,</i>

01:24.000 --> 01:27.504
<i>John Shuster and his team</i>
<i>are the favorites here.</i>

